## About

Trap command monitors the application, to stop the application if it exceeds a set threshold.
I propose this command for paformance test usage.
Application is stopped by Director::stopAnimation.
## Example

```
// set threthold. fire when FPS falls below 30.
> trap fps 30

// start inspecting.
> trap start

// (play something heavy scene)
traped by fps threshold.

// show scene graph that saved just trap. 
// to use the scenegraph subcommand instead of default scenegraph command,
// because performFunctionInCocosThread dose not work when director stopped.
> trap scenegraph

// resume application
> director start
```

(`director start` is not work on iOS. See Issue #15119)
